The 2013 Grindhouse blu-ray release of (the Columbia owned) Corruption,
provides home viewers not only with an exceptional transfer of a
UK horror gem, but also presents both the UK/US Theatrical cut AND
the rarely seen, unedited, International (Continental) Version
(complete with the topless prostitute / beheading scene) and plenty
of blood fueled psycho frenzy.
The main difference is that in the international version, the murder
of the prostitute (played by an entirely different actress) has her
topless, followed by a blood-soaked scalpel carving and the dialogue
and execution are also different.Undoubtedly Peter Cushing's most
'shocking' venture in film and not one that he was particularly fond of.

